[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

5
00:00:45,782 --> 00:00:47,110
[under professional supervision.]

6
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:50,188
[Episode 3]

7
00:00:57,377 --> 00:01:00,028
They offered to help me
blow the Oh Kwang Jae case wide open.

8
00:01:00,028 --> 00:01:02,938
So I almost just went ahead and
blew the whole thing wide open, but...

9
00:01:02,938 --> 00:01:06,483
I'm giving you one last chance.

10
00:01:11,947 --> 00:01:15,781
[Kwon Se Myeong]

11
00:01:33,385 --> 00:01:37,171
It looks like she's about
to get into another car.

12
00:01:57,444 --> 00:02:00,063
Got her.

13
00:02:08,139 --> 00:02:11,292
Kwon Se Myeong.

14
00:02:15,096 --> 00:02:17,789
Prosecutor Bang!

15
00:02:39,587 --> 00:02:40,979
Miss,

16
00:02:40,979 --> 00:02:42,819
bring me every fish they have in this place.

17
00:02:42,819 --> 00:02:46,041
I'm about to keep this place running all night!

18
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:48,292
[Chu Sang Ah still in talks with the old man]

19
00:02:48,292 --> 00:02:50,128
Dear Prosecutor Bang.

20
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:52,475
Yes, sir.

21
00:02:52,475 --> 00:02:54,471
I still

22
00:02:54,471 --> 00:02:58,916
get a real kick out of
how we screwed Lee Yang Mi over.

23
00:02:58,916 --> 00:03:01,556
You know I didn't grow up in the mud.
I've got a soft heart.

24
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:06,105
Then I'll make sure
that heart of yours stays protected.

25
00:03:06,105 --> 00:03:07,970
And this...

26
00:03:07,970 --> 00:03:11,272
is how I feel about our future.

27
00:03:11,272 --> 00:03:15,948
Oh man, it's just amazing.
I've never gotten a gift in my life.

28
00:03:15,948 --> 00:03:19,324
Look at you two.
What is this, the love story of the century?

29
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:20,395
Sir,

30
00:03:20,395 --> 00:03:23,509
just polish him up first,
then get him into the presidential campaign.

31
00:03:23,509 --> 00:03:26,780
Jumping straight to a presidential campaign?

32
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:27,925
Alright,

33
00:03:27,925 --> 00:03:30,159
the nomination comes first.

34
00:03:30,159 --> 00:03:33,238
I'll start from the bottom
and learn step by step.

35
00:03:33,238 --> 00:03:35,936
We're bringing in a rising star.

36
00:03:35,936 --> 00:03:37,426
No reason to say no.

37
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:39,270
Alright, let's make it happen.

38
00:03:39,270 --> 00:03:42,783
I'll give it my all.

39
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:48,142
Oh, hello.

40
00:03:48,142 --> 00:03:49,688
This was supposed to be
Prosecutor Bang's setup.

41
00:03:49,688 --> 00:03:51,419
What took you so long?

42
00:03:51,419 --> 00:03:53,892
It's been a while, sir.
I look forward to working with you.

43
00:03:53,892 --> 00:03:56,111
Prosecutor Bang.

44
00:03:56,111 --> 00:03:59,312
I knew you'd make your move sooner or later.

45
00:03:59,312 --> 00:04:02,625
- Let's do good work.
- Likewise, sir.

46
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:13,430
Hi, I'm here too.

47
00:04:13,430 --> 00:04:18,051
You know,
I didn't think that snake would tag along.

48
00:04:18,051 --> 00:04:21,411
Running into someone
from the same household here of all places.

49
00:04:21,411 --> 00:04:23,513
You must've been in a rush
over this Mayor Nam case,

50
00:04:23,513 --> 00:04:25,157
showing up somewhere like this.

51
00:04:25,157 --> 00:04:28,268
You really don't waste any time.

52
00:04:31,110 --> 00:04:33,027
Stay out of it.

53
00:04:33,027 --> 00:04:34,724
Wait...

54
00:04:34,724 --> 00:04:37,688
With this lineup,
I guess sitting together's off the table.

55
00:04:37,688 --> 00:04:39,232
Normally, yeah...

56
00:04:39,232 --> 00:04:41,361
but we can make it work today.

57
00:04:41,361 --> 00:04:43,855
Right?

58
00:04:43,855 --> 00:04:46,107
Right.

59
00:04:46,107 --> 00:04:48,641
Right.

60
00:05:02,009 --> 00:05:05,308
Still got that wild streak.

61
00:05:12,823 --> 00:05:16,709
That's why I always had a soft spot for you.

62
00:05:17,443 --> 00:05:19,809
Sir,

63
00:05:19,809 --> 00:05:24,289
this isn't the time to get sentimental.

64
00:05:24,289 --> 00:05:27,169
Park Jae Sang

65
00:05:27,169 --> 00:05:30,196
is getting out soon.

66
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:37,410
You know

67
00:05:37,410 --> 00:05:40,680
he has a copy of the Oh Kwang Jae file

68
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,603
with your name in it.

69
00:05:46,523 --> 00:05:50,016
If that resurfaces,

70
00:05:51,243 --> 00:05:54,916
you'll be in deep trouble too.

71
00:06:01,272 --> 00:06:04,645
My dad's got plenty of sins too.

72
00:06:04,645 --> 00:06:07,640
For a guy who never trusts anyone,

73
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:10,079
he got played by some hack fortune teller,

74
00:06:10,079 --> 00:06:12,650
took in the wrong second wife,

75
00:06:12,650 --> 00:06:17,078
and made a real mess of the family in the end.

76
00:06:17,078 --> 00:06:18,503
Darn it.

77
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:21,632
Why's he talking like that? So trashy.

78
00:06:21,632 --> 00:06:23,285
Hey, mutt.

79
00:06:23,285 --> 00:06:26,425
Know your place.

80
00:06:27,782 --> 00:06:29,860
You run wild every night

81
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,391
at that secluded Yangpyeong villa,
getting filthy.

82
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,143
You think you're better than everyone else?

83
00:06:33,143 --> 00:06:35,509
Cut the crap.

84
00:06:35,509 --> 00:06:36,646
Director Lee,

85
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:39,113
I know you're on edge about Mayor Nam,

86
00:06:39,113 --> 00:06:40,317
but let's just enjoy tonight.

87
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:42,090
Right.

88
00:06:42,090 --> 00:06:46,160
Tonight is for Prosecutor Bang.

89
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:48,100
Oh, right.

90
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:51,947
I should start calling him Assemblyman Bang.

91
00:06:51,947 --> 00:06:54,664
What is this vibe?

92
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:57,430
You're giving Bang Tae Seop the nomination?

93
00:06:57,430 --> 00:06:58,731
You know...

94
00:06:58,731 --> 00:07:00,814
I just did what needed to be done.

95
00:07:00,814 --> 00:07:03,465
But if I'm offered the nomination,
I'd be honored to accept.

96
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:06,944
Come on, we'd be the honored ones.

97
00:07:06,944 --> 00:07:08,136
Thank you.

98
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,558
Alright, cheers.

99
00:07:09,558 --> 00:07:11,991
Thank you.

100
00:07:46,744 --> 00:07:49,597
Bang Tae Seop.

101
00:07:49,597 --> 00:07:53,237
You know what celebrities
and politicians have in common?

102
00:07:53,237 --> 00:07:55,001
They live and die by their image.

103
00:07:55,001 --> 00:07:58,634
Which means they can be torn down in public.

104
00:07:59,822 --> 00:08:05,048
And that just happens to be my specialty.

105
00:08:07,118 --> 00:08:10,339
You made a big mistake.

106
00:08:13,058 --> 00:08:18,031
Before long,
you'll be begging me for forgiveness.

107
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:28,007
Lee Yang Mi.

108
00:08:28,007 --> 00:08:30,857
This is just the beginning.

109
00:08:30,857 --> 00:08:35,954
Once I get my teeth into someone
with as much to lose as you...

110
00:08:35,954 --> 00:08:38,860
Yeah, we'll see

111
00:08:41,314 --> 00:08:43,909
how far I take it.

112
00:08:44,911 --> 00:08:47,402
Your little love story alone is

113
00:08:47,402 --> 00:08:51,949
more than enough ammo for someone like me.

114
00:09:06,787 --> 00:09:10,887
I was debating whether to tell you...

115
00:09:10,887 --> 00:09:15,872
That tax scandal that blew up
when Chu Sang Ah fought her old agency.

116
00:09:15,872 --> 00:09:19,005
That was me.

117
00:09:20,694 --> 00:09:21,811
What are you talking about?

118
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:26,570
She was getting way too cocky,
hiding behind Chairman Kwon.

119
00:09:26,570 --> 00:09:30,103
So I lined up a few reporters
and made sure she got a taste of reality.

120
00:09:30,103 --> 00:09:33,060
That's how I operate.

121
00:09:33,060 --> 00:09:35,506
Got it?

122
00:09:37,075 --> 00:09:39,746
Do you even know what that put Sang Ah through?

123
00:09:39,746 --> 00:09:42,932
That was the point. Not my problem.

124
00:09:43,991 --> 00:09:46,490
Driver Kang.

125
00:09:49,437 --> 00:09:52,008
And that Oh Kwang Jae case you had lined up.

126
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:54,955
I'm kicking that project into gear.

127
00:09:54,955 --> 00:09:58,674
Big budget, so... stay tuned.

128
00:10:07,732 --> 00:10:09,385
Lee Yang Mi.

129
00:10:09,385 --> 00:10:11,277
I don't know what game you're playing,

130
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:13,238
but I was in charge of that case.

131
00:10:13,238 --> 00:10:16,617
Chu Sang Ah is clean.

132
00:10:18,591 --> 00:10:20,848
You still don't know

133
00:10:20,848 --> 00:10:25,494
what Chu Sang Ah really looks like.

134
00:10:39,593 --> 00:10:42,393
Chu Sang Ah.

135
00:10:42,986 --> 00:10:47,166
You didn't have to go that far back then.

136
00:10:50,569 --> 00:10:55,603
Looks like you're here
to have Park Jae Sang silenced.

137
00:10:56,532 --> 00:11:01,598
But I'm past the point of losing sleep
over a piece of paper like that.

138
00:11:02,739 --> 00:11:05,152
You, on the other hand...

139
00:11:05,152 --> 00:11:07,556
with blood on your hands,

140
00:11:07,556 --> 00:11:10,569
that's a different story.

141
00:11:14,601 --> 00:11:17,067
Sir...

142
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:23,183
You're coming to me for this?

143
00:11:24,901 --> 00:11:28,821
You should be taking a hard look
at your husband first.

144
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:36,159
What are you talking about?

145
00:11:46,085 --> 00:11:50,419
How far do you trust Bang Tae Seop?

146
00:13:29,978 --> 00:13:31,686
2018.

147
00:13:31,686 --> 00:13:34,492
The Oh Kwang Jae murder at Seogwang Hotel.

148
00:13:34,492 --> 00:13:35,685
[Choi Ji Ho's Fact Check]

149
00:13:35,685 --> 00:13:39,270
I first got interested in this case
because of Chu Sang Ah.

150
00:13:39,270 --> 00:13:42,045
But I really started digging

151
00:13:42,045 --> 00:13:44,525
after I saw a photo of Park Jae Sang,

152
00:13:44,525 --> 00:13:46,982
who was arrested as the prime suspect.

153
00:13:46,982 --> 00:13:48,445
[Connection, Contract killing, Confession]
Alright.

154
00:13:48,445 --> 00:13:52,696
For those of you who aren't familiar
with the Oh Kwang Jae case...

155
00:13:52,696 --> 00:13:54,506
[The Oh Kwang Jae Murder Case]
[Three Lives, Tightly Entangled]

156
00:13:54,506 --> 00:13:55,869
[Why Was the Actress Named?]

157
00:13:55,869 --> 00:13:59,783
[Chu Sang Ah hires her bodyguard,
Park Jae Sang, to carry out the hit]

158
00:13:59,783 --> 00:14:01,640
[Admits to killing agency CEO Oh Kwang Jae]

159
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,347
[What was their relationship?]

160
00:14:03,347 --> 00:14:04,423
[Oh Kwang Jae &amp; Chu Sang Ah Interview]
[A radiant smile]

161
00:14:04,423 --> 00:14:08,493
Who was Oh Kwang Jae,

162
00:14:08,493 --> 00:14:12,380
[Korea's reigning romance queen]
the man who made top star Chu Sang Ah

163
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:15,398
[Let's meet the hottest star, Sang Ah]
and ended up the victim of this brutal murder?

164
00:14:15,398 --> 00:14:16,908
[Who is Oh Kwang Jae?]
Oh Kwang Jae was

165
00:14:16,908 --> 00:14:21,378
a powerhouse in Korean cinema,
known as the Midas touch of Chungmuro.

166
00:14:21,378 --> 00:14:23,905
She's got that natural star quality
and the grit to back it up.

167
00:14:23,905 --> 00:14:27,992
I knew she'd go beyond Korea
and become a global star.

168
00:14:27,992 --> 00:14:33,182
He's especially known as the producer
who turned Chu Sang Ah into a top star.

169
00:14:33,182 --> 00:14:35,416
[The man who made her who she is today]

170
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:36,730
But just

171
00:14:36,730 --> 00:14:40,166
as he was about to take a major leap
through a partnership with WR Group,

172
00:14:40,166 --> 00:14:41,719
he was suddenly murdered.

173
00:14:41,719 --> 00:14:43,612
[The Oh Kwang Jae Murder Case]

174
00:14:43,612 --> 00:14:47,380
The killer was Park Jae Sang,
Chu Sang Ah's bodyguard.

175
00:14:47,380 --> 00:14:50,730
A brutal, cold-blooded murder.
Oh Kwang Jae was killed by Park Jae Sang.

176
00:14:50,730 --> 00:14:53,135
This man right here

177
00:14:53,135 --> 00:14:57,504
is Park Jae Sang,
who was arrested as the suspect at the time.

178
00:14:57,504 --> 00:14:59,528
I mean...

179
00:14:59,528 --> 00:15:02,908
he doesn't exactly look like someone
who could hurt a fly.

180
00:15:02,908 --> 00:15:04,725
It got me curious.

181
00:15:04,725 --> 00:15:09,029
How did someone like him end up the suspect
in such a brutal murder?

182
00:15:09,029 --> 00:15:09,891
[The Oh Kwang Jae Murder Case]

183
00:15:09,891 --> 00:15:11,789
So who turned

184
00:15:11,789 --> 00:15:17,402
this gentle guy's world upside down?

185
00:15:20,799 --> 00:15:22,959
But then...

186
00:15:22,959 --> 00:15:26,070
all the case files, the articles.

187
00:15:26,070 --> 00:15:28,227
Every last one of them just vanished.

188
00:15:28,227 --> 00:15:29,307
[Page Not Found]

189
00:15:29,307 --> 00:15:30,939
[The Oh Kwang Jae Murder Case]

190
00:15:30,939 --> 00:15:32,663
[No results found for
"The Oh Kwang Jae Murder Case"]

191
00:15:32,663 --> 00:15:36,203
Raises a pretty obvious question, doesn't it?

192
00:15:37,629 --> 00:15:40,755
There's someone behind this.

193
00:15:47,699 --> 00:15:50,537
So I started digging deeper.

194
00:15:50,537 --> 00:15:54,257
[Did Chu Sang Ah not know?
No, she was always at the center of it]

195
00:15:59,980 --> 00:16:03,134
Then one day,

196
00:16:03,134 --> 00:16:05,920
it hit me.

197
00:16:08,181 --> 00:16:11,534
What if I go beyond the gossip...

198
00:16:11,534 --> 00:16:14,550
and find something more direct?

199
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:16,580
So I

200
00:16:16,580 --> 00:16:19,717
went straight to the prison.

201
00:16:19,717 --> 00:16:22,245
To meet Park Jae Sang.

202
00:16:22,245 --> 00:16:25,011
It's fine. I'll just come back.

203
00:16:25,011 --> 00:16:27,782
Man... came all this way.

204
00:16:27,782 --> 00:16:29,399
[Cheongseong Penitentiary]
See you next time.

205
00:16:29,399 --> 00:16:30,750
He wouldn't see me.

206
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:33,950
So I kept going back. Again and again.

207
00:16:33,950 --> 00:16:38,899
And then one day, he reached out first.
Said he'd meet me.

208
00:16:38,899 --> 00:16:41,806
Cheongseong Penitentiary.

209
00:16:43,092 --> 00:16:44,823
Look at this.

210
00:16:44,823 --> 00:16:46,929
Creepy, right?

211
00:16:46,929 --> 00:16:49,042
[Cheongseong Penitentiary]

212
00:17:02,857 --> 00:17:04,989
Hello, Mr. Park Jae Sang.

213
00:17:04,989 --> 00:17:08,895
He looked just like his photo. Real harmless.

214
00:17:08,895 --> 00:17:11,278
He wouldn't say why he wanted to meet.

215
00:17:11,278 --> 00:17:14,790
I figured there had to be a reason,
so I waited.

216
00:17:14,790 --> 00:17:18,424
Then, right before his release...

217
00:17:18,424 --> 00:17:22,970
He told me something shocking.

218
00:17:24,435 --> 00:17:27,425
After Han Ji Soo died,

219
00:17:27,425 --> 00:17:30,855
Chu Sang Ah refused to shoot
and started spiraling.

220
00:17:30,855 --> 00:17:35,088
So Oh Kwang Jae put me on her security detail.

221
00:17:35,088 --> 00:17:37,901
That's how we met.

222
00:17:39,005 --> 00:17:42,771
I had no idea it would end up like this...

223
00:17:48,701 --> 00:17:51,871
I'll tell you the rest once I'm out.

224
00:17:51,871 --> 00:17:55,078
Chu Sang Ah, and Park Jae Sang...

225
00:17:55,078 --> 00:17:59,918
The shocking truth behind it all.

226
00:18:03,487 --> 00:18:06,280
Next time.

227
00:18:07,467 --> 00:18:09,704
Next time,

228
00:18:09,704 --> 00:18:13,634
we'll have Park Jae Sang here with us,
in person.

229
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:19,474
We'll get into the truth behind all of this.

230
00:18:19,474 --> 00:18:21,627
Bye!

231
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:07,423
I got this.

232
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:31,567
Let's go, 500 calories!
Get those legs up higher!

233
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:35,603
Now let go and jump with your arms out!

234
00:19:36,244 --> 00:19:38,511
- You got this!
- I can't!

235
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:40,471
Good, grab on again.

236
00:19:40,471 --> 00:19:43,892
Take it easy. You're pushing me too hard!

237
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:51,179
Let's call it here for today.

238
00:19:57,611 --> 00:20:00,616
Park Jae Sang gets out today,
so I'm on my way to pick him up.

239
00:20:00,616 --> 00:20:04,246
I'll get the recording as soon as I see him.

240
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:09,342
I watched your last episode.

241
00:20:09,342 --> 00:20:12,134
It felt a little slow.

242
00:20:12,134 --> 00:20:16,425
The pacing is loose. It really drags.

243
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:18,426
Everyone's watching shorts these days.

244
00:20:18,426 --> 00:20:22,430
If you go all artsy like a European film,
we're dead in the water.

245
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:26,018
I'll push him harder this time.

246
00:20:26,746 --> 00:20:28,416
Still...

247
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:30,703
must be nice having money behind you.

248
00:20:30,703 --> 00:20:32,580
The quality's definitely improved.

249
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:36,867
Maybe let's call it dedication, not money.

250
00:20:36,867 --> 00:20:38,337
Sure.

251
00:20:38,337 --> 00:20:42,179
Then show me more of that dedication.

252
00:20:45,981 --> 00:20:47,959
That's Park Jae Sang's booking fee.

253
00:20:47,959 --> 00:20:50,727
By the way, is he still hung up on her?

254
00:20:50,727 --> 00:20:53,578
Selling out Chu Sang Ah's recording this cheap?

255
00:20:53,578 --> 00:20:56,011
He's probably

256
00:20:56,011 --> 00:20:57,495
blinded by revenge

257
00:20:57,495 --> 00:21:00,295
more than money.

258
00:21:02,359 --> 00:21:04,864
Nice line.

259
00:21:04,864 --> 00:21:06,140
See,

260
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:10,725
I may not trust you,
but I trust that mouth of yours.

261
00:21:10,725 --> 00:21:12,752
Thank you.

262
00:21:12,752 --> 00:21:15,238
You can go now.

263
00:21:29,632 --> 00:21:32,249
Choi Ji Ho's on the move.
You're not in position yet?

264
00:21:32,249 --> 00:21:35,128
Buy me a little more time.

265
00:21:36,649 --> 00:21:40,843
- Too many eyes around. Got held up.
- Darn it.

266
00:21:59,122 --> 00:22:00,925
Three minutes.

267
00:22:00,925 --> 00:22:03,121
Got it.

268
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:08,537
Oh my!

269
00:22:13,737 --> 00:22:17,253
What do I do... I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

270
00:22:17,253 --> 00:22:19,213
I-It's fine.

271
00:22:19,213 --> 00:22:21,800
Wait.

272
00:22:25,813 --> 00:22:28,193
This is

273
00:22:28,193 --> 00:22:30,266
really expensive, isn't it?

274
00:22:30,266 --> 00:22:31,979
Sorry?

275
00:22:31,979 --> 00:22:36,217
I got the same brand for a friend once,

276
00:22:36,217 --> 00:22:38,604
so I can tell.

277
00:22:38,604 --> 00:22:40,526
I said it's fine.

278
00:22:40,526 --> 00:22:42,639
Really, it's fine.

279
00:22:44,823 --> 00:22:47,416
Wait...

280
00:22:48,356 --> 00:22:51,583
Haven't we met somewhere before?

281
00:22:53,150 --> 00:22:56,820
Well, I'm a fairly well-known figure,

282
00:22:56,820 --> 00:22:58,677
so that's probably it.

283
00:22:58,677 --> 00:23:00,953
I see.

284
00:23:07,805 --> 00:23:10,524
Mission complete.

285
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,635
Hey.

286
00:23:23,472 --> 00:23:25,972
You are

287
00:23:27,077 --> 00:23:29,505
a well-known leech.

288
00:23:32,384 --> 00:23:35,724
What did you just say?

289
00:23:36,490 --> 00:23:40,377
Keep feeding off

290
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:43,622
other people's lives like that,

291
00:23:43,622 --> 00:23:47,048
it'll come back around and bite you.

292
00:23:55,908 --> 00:23:58,195
Who are you?

293
00:23:58,195 --> 00:24:00,161
See you around,

294
00:24:00,161 --> 00:24:02,834
leech.

295
00:24:02,834 --> 00:24:05,773
Doors closing.

296
00:24:17,187 --> 00:24:19,190
We need to grab that bastard Choi Ji Ho

297
00:24:19,190 --> 00:24:21,710
before he gets his hands on the recording.

298
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:24,674
I planted a tracker on his car.

299
00:24:24,674 --> 00:24:29,001
Looks like he just met Lee Yang Mi
and is heading to pick up Park Jae Sang.

300
00:24:29,001 --> 00:24:33,517
I'll stay on him. I'll call you.

301
00:25:01,843 --> 00:25:04,537
Sir...

302
00:25:04,537 --> 00:25:08,549
Your disciplinary hearing's been called in.

303
00:25:11,710 --> 00:25:14,237
About time.

304
00:25:14,237 --> 00:25:15,857
Sorry?

305
00:25:15,857 --> 00:25:18,317
They took long enough.

306
00:25:18,317 --> 00:25:20,562
I knew he was trouble,

307
00:25:20,562 --> 00:25:23,402
but trying to make himself a star?

308
00:25:23,402 --> 00:25:26,728
How dare he go after
the Chief Prosecutor's in-laws...

309
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:29,365
My apologies, sir.

310
00:25:29,365 --> 00:25:30,487
Chief Prosecutor,

311
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:32,995
if we apply a violation of
the Prosecutor Ethics Code,

312
00:25:32,995 --> 00:25:36,874
we can go as far as suspension.

313
00:25:36,874 --> 00:25:38,385
Do it.

314
00:25:38,385 --> 00:25:42,561
Suspend Bang Tae Seop effective immediately.

315
00:25:43,966 --> 00:25:45,456
How's everyone doing?

316
00:25:45,456 --> 00:25:47,877
Sorry I'm late to my own show.

317
00:25:47,877 --> 00:25:51,088
How dare...

318
00:25:51,088 --> 00:25:54,406
When I was loyal to the organization,
I didn't even get a mention.

319
00:25:54,406 --> 00:25:56,603
Now I slip up once,

320
00:25:56,603 --> 00:25:58,653
and you all throw a party in my name.

321
00:25:58,653 --> 00:26:01,859
- I'm honored.
- Hey, Tae Seop.

322
00:26:05,824 --> 00:26:08,388
I'm the one who dragged all of you
into this room,

323
00:26:08,388 --> 00:26:12,078
so if I'm getting suspended,
you should be right there with me.

324
00:26:12,078 --> 00:26:14,569
Director Byun, then...

325
00:26:14,569 --> 00:26:16,653
Should we start with the Samgwang Hotel case?

326
00:26:16,653 --> 00:26:18,829
You little...

327
00:26:19,795 --> 00:26:20,978
So,

328
00:26:20,978 --> 00:26:25,938
I'll have to decline your suspension.

329
00:26:28,937 --> 00:26:31,008
This rotten organization?

330
00:26:31,008 --> 00:26:32,708
I'm walking out

331
00:26:32,708 --> 00:26:35,001
[Letter of Resignation]
on my own.

332
00:26:35,001 --> 00:26:36,792
Has he lost his mind?

333
00:26:36,792 --> 00:26:38,225
Goodbye.

334
00:26:38,225 --> 00:26:39,455
Bye.

335
00:26:39,455 --> 00:26:41,182
Hey, Tae Seop.

336
00:26:41,182 --> 00:26:42,995
Hey!

337
00:26:42,995 --> 00:26:44,853
Bang Tae Seop!

338
00:26:44,853 --> 00:26:46,230
You little punk...

339
00:26:46,230 --> 00:26:47,817
Hey!

340
00:26:47,817 --> 00:26:52,462
You're just going to blow this up
and walk away?

341
00:26:57,789 --> 00:27:00,508
Tae Seop...

342
00:27:00,508 --> 00:27:03,326
The stuff I told you to hide...

343
00:27:03,326 --> 00:27:06,733
that stays buried, right?

344
00:27:06,733 --> 00:27:08,450
Hard to say.

345
00:27:08,450 --> 00:27:11,747
I might be giving you a call down the line.

346
00:27:11,747 --> 00:27:14,265
You can settle what you owe me then.

347
00:27:14,265 --> 00:27:16,438
I'm off.

348
00:27:18,399 --> 00:27:20,912
Darn it.

349
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:32,350
[Mayor Nam Hye Hoon Holds
Emergency Press Conference]

350
00:27:32,350 --> 00:27:34,903
[Mayor Nam Emergency Press Conference]

351
00:27:34,903 --> 00:27:39,117
[Nam Hye Hoon Admits to Sex Bribery]
[Resigns as Mayor of Seoam]

352
00:27:42,897 --> 00:27:45,270
Nice.

353
00:27:51,433 --> 00:27:54,179
There he is!

354
00:28:00,721 --> 00:28:02,490
Are you stepping down from the prosecution?

355
00:28:02,490 --> 00:28:03,807
Were you under internal pressure?

356
00:28:03,807 --> 00:28:07,480
Mayor Nam just resigned.
As the whistleblower, how do you feel?

357
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:11,173
What are your plans going forward?

358
00:28:12,399 --> 00:28:14,693
I'm being forced out for exposing corruption
within the organization,

359
00:28:14,693 --> 00:28:16,241
so as of today,

360
00:28:16,241 --> 00:28:20,430
I'm stepping down as a prosecutor.

361
00:28:20,430 --> 00:28:22,409
But here and now,

362
00:28:22,409 --> 00:28:26,314
I'd like to announce a new beginning.

363
00:28:26,314 --> 00:28:27,845
I, Bang Tae Seop,

364
00:28:27,845 --> 00:28:29,564
will be entering

365
00:28:29,564 --> 00:28:32,236
this general election

366
00:28:32,236 --> 00:28:35,588
as Changjo Party's first recruited candidate.

367
00:28:35,588 --> 00:28:37,805
No matter what challenges come my way,

368
00:28:37,805 --> 00:28:40,134
I will stand firm,

369
00:28:40,134 --> 00:28:42,951
never bow to power,

370
00:28:42,951 --> 00:28:47,962
and serve only the people.

371
00:28:47,962 --> 00:28:49,679
Thank you.

372
00:28:49,679 --> 00:28:51,063
One more comment, please!

373
00:28:51,063 --> 00:28:53,432
Did you always plan to go into politics?
Please answer.

374
00:28:53,432 --> 00:28:55,236
When will you officially begin your campaign?

375
00:28:55,236 --> 00:28:57,333
Please respond.

376
00:28:57,333 --> 00:28:59,509
Is that true?

377
00:29:02,621 --> 00:29:04,186
Over here, please!

378
00:29:04,186 --> 00:29:06,609
Please answer!

379
00:29:16,161 --> 00:29:18,437
First of all,

380
00:29:18,437 --> 00:29:21,287
I apologize for the disruption.

381
00:29:21,287 --> 00:29:23,730
I'm sorry.

382
00:29:24,961 --> 00:29:28,371
It's not her fault, but still,

383
00:29:28,371 --> 00:29:32,772
with the shoot getting canceled and delayed,

384
00:29:32,772 --> 00:29:36,348
the losses are significant.

385
00:29:36,348 --> 00:29:39,472
We really have no excuse.

386
00:29:39,472 --> 00:29:42,272
But this film is

387
00:29:43,525 --> 00:29:45,889
her comeback project,

388
00:29:45,889 --> 00:29:48,189
so you know

389
00:29:48,189 --> 00:29:52,819
how important it is to both of us.

390
00:29:52,819 --> 00:29:55,517
- Maybe we can have some dinner...
- I'll cover...

391
00:29:55,517 --> 00:29:59,070
the additional production costs within reason.

392
00:30:00,657 --> 00:30:05,057
What matters most is
finishing the film properly.

393
00:30:05,057 --> 00:30:08,747
As for the delays from the canceled shoot,

394
00:30:08,747 --> 00:30:11,497
let's discuss compensation separately.

395
00:30:12,614 --> 00:30:17,114
She is willing to go this far,

396
00:30:17,114 --> 00:30:18,847
so I hope you can ease up a bit.

397
00:30:18,847 --> 00:30:21,767
You can go over the details with him.

398
00:30:21,767 --> 00:30:23,869
I need to take this.

399
00:30:23,869 --> 00:30:24,906
Okay.

400
00:30:24,906 --> 00:30:28,704
Let's step outside and talk specifics.

401
00:30:45,316 --> 00:30:47,073
I'm out.

402
00:30:47,073 --> 00:30:49,249
Where should we meet?

403
00:30:49,249 --> 00:30:51,569
Jae Sang,

404
00:30:52,443 --> 00:30:55,809
today is not a good time.

405
00:30:55,809 --> 00:30:58,386
I told you this was your last chance.

406
00:30:58,386 --> 00:31:00,593
Why do you keep making me out

407
00:31:00,593 --> 00:31:03,369
to be the bad guy?

408
00:31:03,369 --> 00:31:07,157
You're the one who pushed me here.

409
00:31:07,157 --> 00:31:10,245
I didn't want this.

410
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:14,566
Chu Sang Ah.

411
00:31:14,566 --> 00:31:16,299
You really

412
00:31:16,299 --> 00:31:19,605
want to see how far I'll take this?

413
00:31:20,799 --> 00:31:25,585
I just can't leave right now.

414
00:31:25,585 --> 00:31:29,345
You said if I killed Oh Kwang Jae,
you'd be with me.

415
00:31:29,345 --> 00:31:33,924
That you'd leave Bang Tae Seop...
Was all of that a lie?

416
00:31:33,924 --> 00:31:37,131
No.

417
00:31:37,131 --> 00:31:40,177
I meant it back then.

418
00:31:41,557 --> 00:31:44,244
You know

419
00:31:45,077 --> 00:31:47,491
I can't do that anymore.

420
00:31:47,491 --> 00:31:48,861
No.

421
00:31:48,861 --> 00:31:52,348
I'm not letting you go.

422
00:31:52,348 --> 00:31:54,746
You wreck my life,
and live with some other guy...

423
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:58,579
and I'm just supposed to sit back and watch?

424
00:31:58,579 --> 00:32:01,373
Not happening.

425
00:32:01,373 --> 00:32:03,906
So come to me.

426
00:32:03,906 --> 00:32:06,766
Keep your promise to me.

427
00:32:06,766 --> 00:32:09,510
Or I'll take this all the way.

428
00:32:09,510 --> 00:32:11,674
I'll expose everything, recordings and all.

429
00:32:11,674 --> 00:32:14,847
I'll show the whole country

430
00:32:15,570 --> 00:32:18,550
what kind of monster you are.

431
00:32:18,550 --> 00:32:21,354
And I'll blow that fake marriage to pieces...

432
00:32:21,354 --> 00:32:24,974
then take you down with me.

433
00:32:24,974 --> 00:32:27,296
Just watch.

434
00:33:09,278 --> 00:33:11,531
I may be leaving the organization,

435
00:33:11,531 --> 00:33:13,283
but if this has helped expose
not just the prosecution,

436
00:33:13,283 --> 00:33:16,406
but the truth of how our system really works,

437
00:33:16,406 --> 00:33:19,130
then I've done my part.

438
00:33:19,130 --> 00:33:20,760
Mr. Bang Tae Seop,

439
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:22,854
thank you for your candid remarks.

440
00:33:22,854 --> 00:33:25,471
You've announced a new beginning today,

441
00:33:25,471 --> 00:33:27,795
and we look forward to what's ahead.

442
00:33:27,795 --> 00:33:30,295
Thank you.

443
00:33:31,168 --> 00:33:34,492
I approached this
as if I were stepping off a cliff.

444
00:33:34,492 --> 00:33:36,542
And I'll keep fighting injustice,

445
00:33:36,542 --> 00:33:40,309
to repay the support and trust you've shown me.

446
00:33:40,309 --> 00:33:42,855
Thank you.

447
00:34:03,096 --> 00:34:06,852
[246-17 Huichang-dong, Gangseo-gu]

448
00:34:23,804 --> 00:34:26,190
You've been through a lot.

449
00:34:26,190 --> 00:34:29,103
Thanks to you, we're off to a good start.

450
00:34:31,697 --> 00:34:34,497
Mind if I take a look?

451
00:34:47,007 --> 00:34:49,634
Well...

452
00:34:49,634 --> 00:34:52,847
How are you planning to release this?

453
00:34:52,847 --> 00:34:54,358
What do you mean?

454
00:34:54,358 --> 00:34:57,620
Are you putting all of it out there?

455
00:35:01,022 --> 00:35:04,361
You're still a softie.

456
00:35:08,359 --> 00:35:11,906
Still hung up on Chu Sang Ah?

457
00:35:14,339 --> 00:35:17,925
She was my first love.

458
00:35:17,925 --> 00:35:20,205
Alright.

459
00:35:22,884 --> 00:35:24,487
Think of it this way.

460
00:35:24,487 --> 00:35:26,511
Even the best ingredients

461
00:35:26,511 --> 00:35:29,095
depend on who's handling them.

462
00:35:29,095 --> 00:35:31,036
They can turn into something great,

463
00:35:31,036 --> 00:35:33,795
something forgettable...

464
00:35:33,795 --> 00:35:36,415
or complete trash.

465
00:35:37,823 --> 00:35:42,170
Chu Sang Ah will come back to you.

466
00:35:42,170 --> 00:35:45,396
I'll handle the recording.

467
00:35:47,436 --> 00:35:50,276
I know what you're worried about.

468
00:35:50,276 --> 00:35:53,729
But I know what you want even better.

469
00:35:54,704 --> 00:35:57,838
I'll make sure you get it.

470
00:35:57,838 --> 00:36:00,724
Just trust me this once.

471
00:36:20,876 --> 00:36:23,456
Here it is.

472
00:36:41,353 --> 00:36:45,552
Feels like something that's been buried
is finally coming back to life.

473
00:37:03,836 --> 00:37:05,828
I

474
00:37:06,456 --> 00:37:09,415
want to be your woman.

475
00:37:11,998 --> 00:37:15,150
I'll give you everything.

476
00:37:16,753 --> 00:37:19,553
So... Jae Sang.

477
00:37:37,984 --> 00:37:40,719
[The real killer behind the Oh Kwang Jae case]

478
00:37:40,719 --> 00:37:42,309
[is Chu Sang Ah]

479
00:37:57,619 --> 00:37:59,913
Bang Tae Seop?

480
00:38:15,877 --> 00:38:18,382
What are you doing?

481
00:38:31,226 --> 00:38:34,064
Hey, leech.

482
00:38:35,753 --> 00:38:38,340
What the hell are you?

483
00:38:52,030 --> 00:38:54,096
Let go!

484
00:38:55,003 --> 00:38:56,300
Bang Tae Seop!

485
00:38:56,300 --> 00:38:58,509
Bang Tae Seop!

486
00:39:03,130 --> 00:39:04,910
Hey.

487
00:39:04,910 --> 00:39:07,027
Take one more step,

488
00:39:07,027 --> 00:39:09,517
and you're dead.

489
00:39:09,517 --> 00:39:13,147
You really think you can say that,
knowing who Chu Sang Ah really is?

490
00:39:13,147 --> 00:39:14,959
You think you know her...

491
00:39:14,959 --> 00:39:16,958
What,

492
00:39:16,958 --> 00:39:20,191
that she asked you to kill Oh Kwang Jae?

493
00:39:20,191 --> 00:39:21,734
So what?

494
00:39:21,734 --> 00:39:25,510
What's the problem, huh?

495
00:39:25,510 --> 00:39:28,288
You already knew...

496
00:39:28,288 --> 00:39:31,863
You knew she put me up to it,
and you threw a murder charge on me?

497
00:39:31,863 --> 00:39:33,134
Hey!

498
00:39:33,134 --> 00:39:37,181
Whatever you and Sang Ah had going on,

499
00:39:37,181 --> 00:39:39,419
you were the one holding the knife.

500
00:39:39,419 --> 00:39:42,318
And you paid for it. Got it?

501
00:39:42,318 --> 00:39:43,506
Fine!

502
00:39:43,506 --> 00:39:47,045
Then let's both go down.

503
00:39:47,045 --> 00:39:51,025
I'll tear you both apart.

504
00:39:54,762 --> 00:39:56,247
Go ahead.

505
00:39:56,247 --> 00:39:58,362
Put it out there.

506
00:39:58,362 --> 00:40:01,009
Did you forget I'm a prosecutor?

507
00:40:01,009 --> 00:40:03,100
You release that,

508
00:40:03,100 --> 00:40:07,723
and you rot in prison for life.

509
00:40:07,723 --> 00:40:09,930
No.

510
00:41:03,228 --> 00:41:06,218
Seven years ago, the Oh Kwang Jae murder case.

511
00:41:06,218 --> 00:41:10,164
The one who ordered
the killing was Chu Sang Ah.

512
00:41:12,075 --> 00:41:14,753
The prosecutor who buried the case

513
00:41:14,753 --> 00:41:16,866
is her now-husband, Bang Tae Seop.

514
00:41:16,866 --> 00:41:20,587
[Oh Kwang Jae's Entertainment List]
[Chu Sang Ah, Investor Kwon Se Myeong]

515
00:41:21,900 --> 00:41:25,352
Before we go back through this couple's past,

516
00:41:25,352 --> 00:41:27,841
[China Expansion &amp; Investment Signing Ceremony]

517
00:41:28,931 --> 00:41:32,644
there's someone you need to know

518
00:41:32,644 --> 00:41:36,110
to understand what really happened.

519
00:41:49,317 --> 00:41:52,057
Actress Han Ji Soo.

520
00:41:57,227 --> 00:41:58,785
A lot of you

521
00:41:58,785 --> 00:42:00,988
[Choi Ji Ho's Fact Check]
have been waiting for this,

522
00:42:00,988 --> 00:42:03,478
and it's something
I've been working on for years,

523
00:42:03,478 --> 00:42:06,973
so this episode will be split into two parts.

524
00:42:08,585 --> 00:42:10,942
First,

525
00:42:10,942 --> 00:42:16,575
let's take a look at Han Ji Soo,
a key figure in the case.

526
00:42:50,736 --> 00:42:51,760
Cut.

527
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:54,420
What was that?

528
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:59,394
No, wait...

529
00:42:59,394 --> 00:43:02,300
I'm sorry.

530
00:43:17,124 --> 00:43:20,717
Don't try to slide this past me.

531
00:43:20,717 --> 00:43:23,721
If you want Sung Yu Mi, bring me Kim Won Bin.

532
00:43:23,721 --> 00:43:28,374
That's how you make a deal, alright?

533
00:43:28,374 --> 00:43:30,378
Tell your director this.

534
00:43:30,378 --> 00:43:32,098
If he keeps this up,

535
00:43:32,098 --> 00:43:36,045
I'll wipe their actors off the board.

536
00:43:36,045 --> 00:43:40,618
I've got a situation on set.
I'll call you later.

537
00:43:40,618 --> 00:43:42,775
Hello, sir.

538
00:43:42,775 --> 00:43:44,702
I should've handled Ji Soo better.

539
00:43:44,702 --> 00:43:47,306
I'm really sorry you had to come
all the way out here.

540
00:43:47,306 --> 00:43:49,003
At this rate,

541
00:43:49,003 --> 00:43:52,809
where do you think we can even use Han Ji Soo?

542
00:44:01,252 --> 00:44:03,276
Where's Ji Soo?

543
00:44:03,276 --> 00:44:04,955
[Sang Ah]

544
00:44:06,179 --> 00:44:10,995
Please... please just pick up.

545
00:44:10,995 --> 00:44:13,292
Ji Soo! Han Ji Soo!

546
00:44:13,292 --> 00:44:15,965
Open the door.

547
00:44:15,965 --> 00:44:17,928
I said I'm not filming!

548
00:44:17,928 --> 00:44:20,906
Hey, CEO Oh is here!

549
00:44:26,640 --> 00:44:28,893
Sir...

550
00:44:28,893 --> 00:44:33,266
Ji Soo, are you okay?

551
00:44:40,069 --> 00:44:43,909
What is it? What's the problem?

552
00:44:48,557 --> 00:44:50,840
Sir.

553
00:44:50,840 --> 00:44:53,239
Why is there another bed scene

554
00:44:53,239 --> 00:44:56,039
that wasn't in the script?

555
00:44:58,081 --> 00:44:59,864
Money. That's all.

556
00:44:59,864 --> 00:45:03,348
That's what people want.

557
00:45:03,348 --> 00:45:05,692
I can't do this anymore.

558
00:45:05,692 --> 00:45:08,336
I'm seeing a psychiatrist, I can't sleep...

559
00:45:08,336 --> 00:45:11,996
At this rate, I feel like I'm going to die.

560
00:45:15,780 --> 00:45:18,580
I feel like dying too.

561
00:45:19,247 --> 00:45:21,404
But a deal's a deal.

562
00:45:21,404 --> 00:45:24,204
You signed, you shoot.

563
00:45:26,326 --> 00:45:27,750
But...

564
00:45:27,750 --> 00:45:29,426
Ji Soo.

565
00:45:29,426 --> 00:45:32,816
You know why we stamp contracts in red?

566
00:45:32,816 --> 00:45:35,762
It means it's written in blood.

567
00:45:35,762 --> 00:45:38,524
Unless you're dead
and there's a death certificate,

568
00:45:38,524 --> 00:45:41,983
you finish what you signed.

569
00:45:44,647 --> 00:45:46,691
This

570
00:45:46,691 --> 00:45:49,983
could go to court.

571
00:46:02,510 --> 00:46:07,412
- Please!
- Alright! She's in the zone. Let's roll.

572
00:46:07,412 --> 00:46:09,766
Where's Kim Jae Won? Get him in here.

573
00:46:09,766 --> 00:46:12,286
Camera up!

574
00:46:17,231 --> 00:46:20,204
What are you doing? Get in position.

575
00:46:24,178 --> 00:46:28,176
Do you have any idea how much money
we're burning while you stall?

576
00:46:28,176 --> 00:46:31,349
Earn your keep.

577
00:46:39,526 --> 00:46:41,383
Mr. Oh Kwang Jae!

578
00:46:41,383 --> 00:46:43,333
Sang Ah.

579
00:46:43,333 --> 00:46:45,426
Sir.

580
00:46:45,426 --> 00:46:49,077
You're still pulling this kind of crap?

581
00:46:49,077 --> 00:46:52,107
Before I expose everything you've pulled

582
00:46:52,107 --> 00:46:55,964
and get you blacklisted from this industry,

583
00:46:55,964 --> 00:46:59,130
you'd better straighten yourself out.

584
00:46:59,871 --> 00:47:01,881
Ji Soo.

585
00:47:01,881 --> 00:47:03,529
- Are you okay?
- Chu Sang Ah.

586
00:47:03,529 --> 00:47:06,855
What do you think you're doing?

587
00:47:06,855 --> 00:47:10,092
I've had enough of your little tantrums.

588
00:47:10,092 --> 00:47:12,116
Step away.

589
00:47:12,116 --> 00:47:14,840
She's done with this film, starting today.

590
00:47:14,840 --> 00:47:16,426
Send over the contract.

591
00:47:16,426 --> 00:47:19,379
I'll cover the penalty.

592
00:47:27,681 --> 00:47:29,962
[Oh Kwang Jae]

593
00:47:52,426 --> 00:47:55,029
Don't take any calls.

594
00:47:55,029 --> 00:47:58,424
Stay here for a while.

595
00:47:58,424 --> 00:48:03,097
I'll talk to a lawyer and sort things out
with CEO Oh's project.

596
00:48:04,610 --> 00:48:06,671
Don't.

597
00:48:06,671 --> 00:48:10,237
I don't want this to get any bigger.

598
00:48:11,065 --> 00:48:14,638
- Ji Soo.
- I'm scared.

599
00:48:37,916 --> 00:48:42,182
If this goes any further,
I feel like it's over for me.

600
00:48:42,982 --> 00:48:45,933
What if he blocks my career...

601
00:48:45,933 --> 00:48:49,679
and I never work again?

602
00:48:51,290 --> 00:48:54,649
Let's just stop here.

603
00:49:01,935 --> 00:49:06,182
Thank you for standing up for me, Sang Ah.

604
00:49:17,301 --> 00:49:21,527
You're not going back to that project, right?

605
00:49:23,992 --> 00:49:26,977
At least, if we cut the scenes
that weren't in the script,

606
00:49:26,977 --> 00:49:29,425
there aren't many shoot days left.

607
00:49:29,425 --> 00:49:34,141
I want to talk to him and just finish it.

608
00:49:39,840 --> 00:49:42,821
I'm worried

609
00:49:44,373 --> 00:49:47,319
this will happen again.

610
00:49:50,107 --> 00:49:53,533
How did it end up like this...

611
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:59,020
I just wanted to be a great actress.

612
00:50:06,310 --> 00:50:09,189
Let's get stronger.

613
00:50:10,263 --> 00:50:13,796
Then no one can push us around.

614
00:50:27,781 --> 00:50:31,627
I heard Chu Sang Ah and Han Ji Soo

615
00:50:31,627 --> 00:50:36,360
had been inseparable since their debut...

616
00:50:36,360 --> 00:50:41,207
but to me, it felt like something more.

617
00:50:41,207 --> 00:50:43,794
It wasn't just friendship,

618
00:50:43,794 --> 00:50:46,566
it was love. Right?

619
00:50:49,086 --> 00:50:50,960
Back then,

620
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:53,956
Chu Sang Ah didn't have
any real scandals with men,

621
00:50:53,956 --> 00:50:57,473
so I figured... maybe that was it.

622
00:50:57,473 --> 00:51:00,619
So she really lost it, huh?

623
00:51:00,619 --> 00:51:03,231
Over Han Ji Soo.

624
00:51:04,716 --> 00:51:08,157
No one in that world could go up

625
00:51:08,157 --> 00:51:11,576
against Oh Kwang Jae.

626
00:51:13,264 --> 00:51:16,723
But Chu Sang Ah started spiraling.

627
00:51:16,723 --> 00:51:18,701
And that spiral

628
00:51:18,701 --> 00:51:21,707
led to murder.

629
00:51:24,420 --> 00:51:27,306
So why did she

630
00:51:28,127 --> 00:51:31,966
want Oh Kwang Jae dead?

631
00:51:34,945 --> 00:51:37,584
What really happened

632
00:51:37,584 --> 00:51:40,172
[Chu Sang Ah Announces Hiatus
Following Han Ji Soo's Death]

633
00:51:40,172 --> 00:51:42,948
between them?

634
00:51:42,948 --> 00:51:46,574
[Chu Sang Ah Cast in Seeds of Tears]

635
00:51:48,543 --> 00:51:50,666
Han Ji Soo, Oh Kwang Jae...

636
00:51:50,666 --> 00:51:53,112
and Chu Sang Ah.

637
00:51:54,402 --> 00:51:57,332
Could there be more

638
00:51:57,332 --> 00:51:59,876
we don't know?

639
00:51:59,876 --> 00:52:02,833
[Han Ji Soo Found Dead at Home
in Apparent Suicide]

640
00:52:02,833 --> 00:52:05,882
[Han Ji Soo Pushes Boundaries
with Consecutive 19+ Roles]

641
00:52:14,208 --> 00:52:17,627
I think everything went wrong

642
00:52:18,227 --> 00:52:21,493
starting that night.

643
00:52:38,652 --> 00:52:41,258
Oh, Ji Soo.

644
00:52:42,418 --> 00:52:43,482
Sir.

645
00:52:43,482 --> 00:52:46,731
Long trip, huh? Come on in.

646
00:52:49,754 --> 00:52:51,544
We're filming today, right?

647
00:52:51,544 --> 00:52:54,951
I didn't see any of the crew.

648
00:53:07,706 --> 00:53:09,706
Sir.

649
00:53:09,706 --> 00:53:12,586
This isn't a shoot, is it?

650
00:53:12,586 --> 00:53:15,859
Something more important.

651
00:53:22,539 --> 00:53:24,743
Chairman, and Chief Prosecutor.

652
00:53:24,743 --> 00:53:26,554
Thank you for your patience.

653
00:53:26,554 --> 00:53:29,039
This is Han Ji Soo,
a new actress I just brought on.

654
00:53:29,039 --> 00:53:35,090
Great voice, and she really knows
how to use her body.

655
00:54:04,428 --> 00:54:06,741
Let go!

656
00:54:08,041 --> 00:54:09,872
Hey.

657
00:54:09,872 --> 00:54:12,414
Easy there.

658
00:54:12,414 --> 00:54:15,801
You almost hurt her.

659
00:54:15,801 --> 00:54:17,681
Ji Soo,

660
00:54:17,681 --> 00:54:20,928
are you okay?

661
00:54:20,928 --> 00:54:24,420
What is this...

662
00:54:24,420 --> 00:54:28,000
Just stay still. Don't make a scene.

663
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:30,933
My apologies, Chairman.

664
00:58:21,844 --> 00:58:25,722
These are the pieces of evidence
found at the Oh Kwang Jae crime scene.

665
00:58:25,722 --> 00:58:29,337
I'll take the fall with you.

666
00:58:29,337 --> 00:58:32,548
What did you do to Ji Soo?

667
00:58:32,548 --> 00:58:35,115
If that gets out, we're finished.

668
00:58:35,115 --> 00:58:36,805
You're no different.

669
00:58:36,805 --> 00:58:39,005
My mistake was marrying a killer.

670
00:58:39,005 --> 00:58:41,142
You're the one who killed him.

671
00:58:41,142 --> 00:58:43,757
Even if you hadn't...

672
00:58:44,564 --> 00:58:47,831
Oh Kwang Jae was going to die anyway.
